data.text: @terra155 @CatPurry9 Wow refused. God, thank heavens Craig Kelly and Pete Evans have been muted. People like them play on people’s fears.

@Tassiedevil5 @CatPurry9 Ouch and yes, am just over the lack of positivity.
My GP told me that his nurse, refused to give the vaccination, think he is now looking for a new one.
@terra155 @CatPurry9 I’ve had 2 lung clots. 1 hospital acquired 1 not. I’ve had my first AZ with no reaction what so ever.  With my reduced lung capacity I’d rather chance AZ than covid.
@CatPurry9 Thanks Cat.  Among my friends (we are all 70/80 age range) it is running about 50/50 some having no reaction at all to the others lots of body aches, chills.

@CatPurry9 @Tassiedevil5 Yes, a tad miffed at lack of info, but a jump to, must be the AZ responsible.  Does nothing to enlist confidence and am tired of pointing out, all vaccines/medicines can have a neg effect 😠
@CatPurry9 My GP says it will take a while because trials only done on smaller numbers & not peer reviewed.  We are in a world wide experimental test lab.   I get my Astrazeneca on Tuesday.
@CatPurry9 The types of clot and the underlying mechanism is certainly higher than ‘baseline’ and without doubt aligned to AZ.

@CatPurry9 Cat - From Reuters "Similarly, most of the cases reported in Europe have occurred in women under 60, though that could be misleading, since Germany and Britain say more women got AstraZeneca's shot than men."   We do seem to be having quite a few men getting these clots.
@CatPurry9 And what preconditions if any these had?
@CatPurry9 30,000 cases and 5000 deaths per yr of non AZ clots
@CatPurry9 I believe it's not but I stand to be corrected if we now have more information on the issue.
